Text.Value: Shar is an abomination. You deceived me.
What, Shar's tenets? If you like...
Maybe both, knowing myself. But yes. Once we've saved ourselves, we can talk more on this.
Remind me.
Though perhaps that might change, if you can show an open mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conceding jus a little towards the player's hurt feelings - but conditionally

Text.Value: I have no problems with Shar worshippers, if that's what concerns you.
Forget it.
I even keep secrets from myself - I had my memories suppressed, so that nothing I knew could be used against the Dark Lady. Once I prove myself, my memories will be restored.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node only if the memory suppression beat wasn't established

Text.Value: That ruined Selûne statue - it made you hesitate.
I... yes, she must. I'll offer thanks to her in my prayers - and we should speak more later. Alone, ideally.
I'm not sorry I kept this from you. Not one bit.

EditorData.NodeContext: unrepentant

Text.Value: I don't quite understand.
You've already pestered me with your notions once today. If I have something to add, I'll tell you.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The player already attempted persuades today - there's no more attempts available until after rest.

Text.Value: Not so. Our youngest are left to fend for themselves in the deepest wilds. They need to survive and navigate home using the Moonmaiden's guiding light.
I bow to Shar also. The Dark Lady must favour us, to have brought us together.
My Lady Shar is the Nightsinger. The patron of darkness and loss.
My apologies. I didn't mean to pry.
Spare me the bluster and threats. If I have something to tell you, I'll tell you.
I can't trust you. Best if we travel separately for now.
I'll decide whether to make a fuss or not. Hard to trust someone who's holding out on me.
Not this again. I told you already - forget it.
There's comfort, yes. But often there has to be pain beforehand...
You should trust me. We're in the same boat, after all.
Change the subject.
You're good company - I'll admit it. I'm sorry you're hindered by that supposed goddess.

EditorData.NodeContext: Backhanded compliment to someone she respects in one sense but is rivalled by in another sense. Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: All we can do is try, I suppose...
Fine, I'll tell you, so long as it spares me your ham-fisted threats.
You pray with such conviction. The presence of your goddess must fill your whole being.
I don't care who you worship. We have bigger problems.
I think I did well by joining you. Most agreeable company.
I assume you've heard of her?
What, you think frolicking in the woods by moonlight amounts to a test? That's nothing. That's just... a childish thing. I don't want to hear any more of it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unimpressed, but giving way to some deja vu disquiet in the back half (this will foreshadow her backstory and abduction as a child). Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I worship Shar, the Mistress of the Night. It is my holy mission to oppose Selûne, her teachings and her followers.
Who says you have to feel anything?
...ah, but there's no bailiff here, is there? Just leagues of wilderness and the dangers lurking within.
That helmeted skeleton we found in the village - there's something you're hiding about it.
Trust me, I am endlessly grateful to not know Selûne.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: How exactly do Shar worshippers turn people to their goddess?
Don't make a fuss, Selûnite - we may be at odds, but I have more important concerns than you right now.
Don't make a big fuss...? You've been lying to me!
You're straight to the point, at least. But still, I'm not sure you are ready for Shar's teachings. Not yet, at least.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This node if SH's approval is greater than 0, less than 10

Text.Value: It's nothing. Really.
More hot air and empty threats. When I want you to know something, I'll tell you.
Tell me what you're hiding, or else.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This active roll is available after the branch is unlocked by one of several events that can trigger in Act 1. It remains available until it is attempted or Shadowheart's Shar Worship is revealed via other means.

Text.Value: Secrecy is everything for Shar's children. It's our code, our creed, our shield.
We can discuss this later. But let's just try a little more honesty going forward.
What, not trying to threaten a confession out of me this time? You'll know if I have anything to tell you.
We have a chance to understand each other - don't you at least want to try?
No, I think you know exactly what I mean.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Fallback question node in case this line of questioning is available but a specific QN referring to a prior situation didn't trigger.

Text.Value: Tell me what you're hiding. Now.
Naturally. We can discuss the Dark Lady another time.
You've a habit of saying all the right things. Either you're very glib or we're kindred spirits.
Most fear the dark, like children, because in darkness they see their fears reflected.
Your goddess is blessed to have such an eloquent servant. Please, show me how you pray to her.
All right. As I said, Shar is my patron, my mistress. Goddess of darkness and loss.
I wish to bear witness to a prayer dedicated to the Nightsinger.
Well if that troubles you, perhaps you should fetch the bailiff to arrest me...

EditorData.NodeContext: Droll.

Text.Value: True. I didn't think you'd react so pragmatically. Perhaps I should have told you sooner.
I didn't expect to see eye to eye with you on this. A pleasant surprise, I'll admit.
But whatever you and I think of each other means little. We stand in opposition - our goddesses have determined it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Sounds like a miserable realm of influence for a deity to hold.
What, now you're resorting to threats? The answer's the same as before - you'll know if I have anything to tell you.
You surprise me - pleasantly. Perhaps I misjudged you.
You're not going to let this go, are you? You might wish you had...
That may be the wisest thing you've ever said.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I don't know what you mean.
Pain. Hope. The promise of better days. All of these are heavy cloaks that bend our backs and burden our hearts.
We destroy false idols, topple corrupt organisations, fight heretics wherever they're found.
Now that you have the truth, please don't make a big fuss about it.
The truth. Now.
Your goddess is blessed to have such an eloquent servant. Please, show me how you pray to her.
A lie of omission at most. I'm sure you have some skeletons of your own hidden away.
Curious. Most are afraid of my Lady.
It sounds evil.
We shed those cloaks. Before Shar we stand gloriously naked, beyond the vanities of mortals.
Like oil complements an open flame, perhaps.

EditorData.NodeContext: Droll, unconvinced. Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I am indeed a disciple of Shar - Mistress of the Night and Lady of Loss.
Now that the truth's out, tell me more.
We've spoken enough of this. I cannot allow your misguided beliefs to poison my mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: This again? You're persistent, I'll give you that.
When we found that Selûne shrine in the cave - you reacted unusually.
Tell me what you're hiding. I can make you talk if I have to.
I don't have to explain myself to you.

EditorData.NodeContext: An abrupt shut down.

Text.Value: I said not for discussion!
You surprise me. And not in a negative sense, I must admit.
I had hoped you might be tactful enough to not pick at that particular scab. Seems I was mistaken.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: That diary we found in Moonhaven - it meant something to you, I know it.
How so? Are you taught to churn your own butter while barely out of swaddling?

EditorData.NodeContext: Derisive. Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Forever, ideally. And you assume too much about what I can and cannot tell.
Honestly, your faith is your own concern. I won't judge, one way or the other.
The night brings comfort. Through loss, we find acceptance. In the arms of the Dark Mother we find peace.
Let's see how open-minded I can be then: tell me more.
Nothing Selûne asks of you can compare to the tests that Lady Shar's children endure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Very well. Perhaps there's potential in you. Let's see how you handle this.
Is this because of what I shared with you? My memory of being saved from the wolf? You're clutching at straws.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: We are far from coddled. All children of Selûne cherish self-reliance. From a young age, we need to fend for ourselves.
We have emptied our hearts of falsehoods. We have vanquished your foes. In the darkness, we see your truth.

EditorData.NodeContext: A prayer, spoken gently, intimately. This is between her, the player and their goddess

Text.Value: Honestly, you just sound jealous.
Don't thank me - I'm breaking Lady Shar's teachings just by doing so... but sometimes you have to be practical.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little embarassed at being thanked

Text.Value: You cannot know for certain. We each walk our own path. Shar, Selûne... nobody can know both.
I didn't agree to join up with a Shar worshipper.
What makes you think I'm hiding anything? If I've something to share, I'll let you know.
In future, I expect you to be honest. Let's leave it at that for now.
I might have to reconsider travelling with you if you keep secrets from me.
Sounds... daunting. I don't think it's for me.
Like I told you before; you'll know if I have anything to tell you.
Then it's your own fault for not asking.

EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER HAS FAILED THREE DAYS OF PERSUASIONS

Text.Value: Gather your thoughts. Then perhaps we can talk some more.
Embrace us, your loyal warriors. Cloak us in your shadow. Guide us to your victory.

EditorData.NodeContext: A prayer, spoken gently, intimately. This is between her, the player and their goddess

Text.Value: All right... you've suffered enough for me to risk a little candour.
Are you sure? You've utterly failed so far. If I have something to tell you, I'll do so when I want to.
I think you know that's not true. I think you know more about the Moonmaiden than you realise...
Fine. Just keep out matters that don't concern you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Terse.

Text.Value: ... yes. I am honoured with her blessing.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little hint of guardedness in this line - in truth, she does not feel her goddess answering her prayers right now.

Text.Value: There has to be something more that draws people to Shar.
We're in this together, but I'll happily go it alone. My faith will keep me company.
As long as we have use for each other, I can bite my tongue and stay my blade. I don't see what more needs to be said on the matter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I suppose some would consider such diplomacy a virtue. Others might just see it as a lack of will.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: You're wiser than most. Many people balk at our doctrine - it's the reason why we cherish secrecy.
I won't cast judgement on your beliefs.
Blessed Nightsinger, witness our adoration. See how we serve you, only you.

EditorData.NodeContext: A prayer, spoken gently, intimately. This is between her, the player and their goddess

Text.Value: I'm well aware of who Shar is - and the dark things she stands for.
I've heard Shar worship is vilified by many - forbidden outright in parts.
My Lady and your moonwitch are at war, so naturally we're enemies... but enemies with a common purpose, for now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: As you worship Selûne, I assume you know of her twin?
But Shar teaches us to step beyond fear. Beyond loss. In darkness we do not hide - we act.
When you put it like that, it seems strangely comforting.
But I suppose there's no harm in learning about the opposition - though I doubt there's much to learn. You Selûnites are coddled, decadent, drunk on hope. Fattened calves, ready for sacrifice.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Fascinating. Please, continue.
Perhaps you'll turn out to be a worthy companion after all.

EditorData.NodeContext: Budding camaraderie.

Text.Value: Inspiring. But what of those who stand against your goddess? How do you sway them?
We have to be honest with each other. What is it you're keeping from me?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This active roll is available after the branch is unlocked by one of several events that can trigger in Act 1. It remains available until it is attempted or Shadowheart's Shar Worship is revealed via other means.

Text.Value: I'd be lying if I said it didn't sound convincing. You should tell me more some time.
Seriously, tell me whatever it is you're hiding or there'll be consequences.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This roll should be available after a day oneroll has been failed. It should have a lower DC than day One.

Text.Value: Not a fast learner, are you? My affairs are my own; I won't be coerced by you.
Very well...
We tear down the lies the world is drunk on: the institutions they trust, the so-called gods they worship. The lives they cling to.
Hrmph. Only if you lack foresight and imagination.
Perhaps once we've saved ourselves from the tadpoles, we can talk more on this.
Then reconsider, if you're sure you can survive without me.
Give it time - and thought.
Humour me. Tell me what your Lady Shar means to you.
Our goddesses are twins - part of a whole. We complement each other.
We can't afford to keep secrets from each other. What are you hiding?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This roll should be available after a day oneroll has been failed. It should have a lower DC than day One.

Text.Value: If you insist. Don't expect to fare well without me to save you.
Ngh... it hurts...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart reacts to the pain of the incurable wound in her right hand. She raises the hand and grimaces in pain. After a brief moment the pain passes and she lowers her hand, face relaxing, returning to default pose.

Text.Value: It's been some time since I met another faithful of Shar. Are you versed in her teachings?
I'm sure you do. But please try to understand that it's not something I can just talk about freely.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If SH approves of the player for a minimum of ten
EditorData.NodeContext: Uncomfortable/a little torn. The player's prying into a personal matter (at the same time, she doesn't have a terrible opinion of them)

Text.Value: I don't know how I feel about this.
I know Shar. She attracts those who've suffered pain, loss. I'm sorry she seduced you.
She doesn't sound very appealing, going by her titles.
You're better company than I would expect, for a Selûnite. Don't let it go to your head, though.

EditorData.NodeContext: Backhanded compliment to someone she respects in one sense but is rivalled by in another sense. Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: Turn to other matters.
What makes you think threats will get you what you want? I've nothing to say to you.
There's often suffering - death even. Many people break before they embrace Shar's truths.
You truly will not give up, will you? I admire your tenacity, if not your powers of persuasion...
I worship Lolth - your secret does not shock me. I've seen and done so much worse.
Perhaps you're right. I'll leave the matter rest.
Whatever secret you're guarding, you can tell me. We need to trust each other.
Gladly.
Let's agree to disagree. This may not be the healthiest topic for us.
You're persistent; I'll give you that. But I'll decide what I share, or don't.
Shar's will shall be done. As sure as night will fall.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Raises her head, strong eye contact on player.

Text.Value: Your blindness as much as my deception, Selûnite. We can talk about this later - if you're willing.
Thank you for telling me, at least.
Tell me - what of those who oppose your Dark Lady? How do you seek to sway them?
If you're attempting to goad me, don't bother. I'm more than familiar with those sort of tricks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Verbal sparring with a Selune-worshipping player. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: I'm not sure I'd agree, but very well. What do you want to know?

EditorData.NodeContext: Skeptical. Fellow cleric of a different god is expressing interest in her faith.

Text.Value: When we entered the old temple of Selûne - you reacted unusually.
No more secrets. Tell me.
What kind of question is that? Of course I am. Are you?
You could have told me. How long were you going to keep this secret?

Synopsis: Default dialogue - the conversation you can have with Shadowheart at any time when she's a member of your party. You can ask her about herself, or events that you've experienced together during your adventures. Her responses to you may differ slightly depending on her current attitude towards you.
